---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="Squatch Marketing's cookie policy. Learn about the minimal cookies used on our website and how to manage them."
>

  <!-- ========== HERO ========== -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[50vh] flex items-center gradient-mesh noise overflow-hidden" aria-label="Cookie Policy Hero">
    <div class="orb-drift absolute top-[10%] right-[15%] w-[500px] h-[500px] rounded-full bg-blue/[0.07] blur-[150px] pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="orb-drift-reverse absolute bottom-[15%] left-[-5%] w-[400px] h-[400px] rounded-full bg-teal/[0.05] blur-[130px] pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 pt-36 lg:pt-44 pb-20">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="reveal mb-6">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3.5 py-1.5 rounded-xl bg-blue/[0.08] border border-blue/[0.12]">
            <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-blue animate-pulse"></div>
            <span class="text-blue text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide">Legal</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <h1 class="reveal reveal-delay-1 font-display font-800 text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] text-white leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.03em]">
          Cookie Policy
        </h1>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-40 bg-gradient-to-t from-void to-transparent pointer-events-none z-10"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- ========== POLICY CONTENT ========== -->
  <section class="relative py-20 bg-void overflow-hidden" aria-label="Cookie Policy Content">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="reveal glass-strong rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12">

        <p class="text-white/40 text-sm mb-8">Last updated: March 29, 2026</p>

        <div class="text-ink-bright text-base leading-relaxed space-y-6">

          <p>
            This Cookie Policy explains how Squatch Marketing ("we," "us," or "our") uses cookies and similar technologies on squatchmarketing.com. We believe in transparency and want you to understand what data is stored when you visit our site.
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-display font-700 text-xl text-white mt-10 mb-4">What Are Cookies?</h2>

          <p>
            Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device (computer, tablet, or phone) when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently and to provide information to website owners. Cookies can be "persistent" (remaining on your device until they expire or are deleted) or "session-based" (deleted when you close your browser).
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-display font-700 text-xl text-white mt-10 mb-4">Our Use of Cookies</h2>

          <p>
            Squatch Marketing uses minimal cookies. We do not use cookies for advertising, tracking, or analytics purposes. Our website does not set any first-party tracking cookies. The only data stored locally is a cookie consent preference in your browser's localStorage.
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-display font-700 text-xl text-white mt-10 mb-4">Types of Cookies on This Site</h2>

          <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-6 mb-6">
            <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
                  <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-display font-700 text-white text-sm">Cookie / Storage</th>
                  <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-display font-700 text-white text-sm">Type</th>
                  <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-display font-700 text-white text-sm">Purpose</th>
                  <th class="py-3 font-display font-700 text-white text-sm">Duration</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-sm">
                <tr class="border-b border-white/[0.04]">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4"><code class="text-teal text-xs bg-white/[0.03] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">cookie-consent</code></td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">localStorage</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Remembers that you accepted the cookie banner so it does not show again</td>
                  <td class="py-3">Persistent</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/[0.04]">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4"><code class="text-teal text-xs bg-white/[0.03] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">__cf_bm</code></td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Third-party (Cloudflare)</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Bot management and security. Helps Cloudflare distinguish humans from bots</td>
                  <td class="py-3">30 minutes</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/[0.04]">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4"><code class="text-teal text-xs bg-white/[0.03] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">__cflb</code></td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Third-party (Cloudflare)</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Load balancing. Ensures your requests are routed to the same server</td>
                  <td class="py-3">Session</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Google Fonts cookies</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">Third-party (Google)</td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-4">May be set when fonts are loaded from Google's servers. Used for font delivery optimization</td>
                  <td class="py-3">Varies</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <p>
            All cookies currently in use on this site are essential or functional. We do not use any marketing, advertising, or analytics cookies.
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-display font-700 text-xl text-white mt-10 mb-4">How to Manage Cookies</h2>

          <p>
            Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can typically find cookie settings in the "Options," "Settings," or "Preferences" menu of your browser. Here are links to cookie management instructions for common browsers:
          </p>

          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-2">
            <li>
              <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal hover:text-teal/80 underline transition-colors">Google Chrome</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enhanced-tracking-protection-firefox-desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal hover:text-teal/80 underline transition-colors">Mozilla Firefox</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal hover:text-teal/80 underline transition-colors">Apple Safari</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/manage-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-view-allow-block-delete-and-use-168dab11-0753-043d-7c16-ede5947fc64d" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-teal hover:text-teal/80 underline transition-colors">Microsoft Edge</a>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <p>
            Please note that blocking all cookies may affect the functionality of some websites. Since our site uses only essential cookies, disabling them should not significantly impact your experience on squatchmarketing.com.
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-display font-700 text-xl text-white mt-10 mb-4">Clearing localStorage</h2>

          <p>
            To clear the cookie consent preference stored in localStorage, you can use your browser's developer tools. In most browsers, open Developer Tools (F12), navigate to the "Application" or "Storage" tab, find "Local Storage," and remove the <code class="text-teal text-xs bg-white/[0.03] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">cookie-consent</code> entry for squatchmarketing.com.
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-display font-700 text-xl text-white mt-10 mb-4">Changes to This Policy</h2>

          <p>
            We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect changes in technology or applicable regulations. Any changes will be posted on this page with a revised "Last updated" date.
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-display font-700 text-xl text-white mt-10 mb-4">Contact Us</h2>

          <p>If you have questions about our use of cookies, you can reach us at:</p>

          <div class="mt-4 space-y-2">
            <p><strong class="text-white">Squatch Marketing</strong></p>
            <p>West Valley City, Utah 84128</p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:marketing@squatchmarketing.com" class="text-teal hover:text-teal/80 underline transition-colors">marketing@squatchmarketing.com</a></p>
            <p>Phone: <a href="tel:801-803-2136" class="text-teal hover:text-teal/80 underline transition-colors">801-803-2136</a></p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
